Package UI

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Reinitializable
    This interface allows its implemented classes to defines a method reset() that allows such class to reinitialize its state variables to its initial values.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CreateUser
    UI dialog to guide new users to create account
    GameFrame
    GameFrame contains GamePanel.this is the window displaying the actual game that user plays.
    GamePanel
    This class has two main functions : Take in key inputs and displays the game on the screen
    HeadToHead  
    InfoPage
    InfoPage provides a quick and easy way to instantiate multiple information dialog.
    Login
    JFrame that displays the login dialog.
    MainMenu
    MainMenu is the first JFrame that the user sees when starting the game.
    MapSelect
    Map selection GUI
    OptionMenu
    Option menu is a menu that can be used to adjust Game Volume (unimplemented) and Game speed (unimplemented) and Game Power ups (unimplemented).
    UIElement
    UIElement is the parent class for almost all of the classes in UI package.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UnimplementedException
    Exception class to mark method as not implemented
